rimer On How The West Uses Right-Wing Ideology To Economically Exploit The Third World</title><link>http://feedproxy.google.com/~r/BlastTheRight/~3/nq3gazwCCe4/137-rights-big-lie-about-upcoming-labor.html</link><author>rational@adelphia.net (Jack Clark)</author><pubDate>Fri, 28 Nov 2008 19:44:36 PST</pubDate><guid isPermaLink="false">tag:blogger.com,1999:blog-15268293.post-5226183919618546906</guid><description>Today, you'll hear how to debunk a bald-faced lie the right is propagating about upcoming, critically important labor union legislation, the Employee Free Choice Act. This bill is labor's number one priority in Congress, and the right has declared war on it.Next, I'll give you a short primer on what I call the four pillars, the four ways the right in the Western world economically exploits the&lt;img src="http://feeds.feedburner.com/~r/BlastTheRight/~4/nq3gazwCCe4" height="1" width="1"/&gt;</description><thr:total xmlns:thr="http://purl.org/syndication/thread/1.0">0</thr:total><media:content url="http://feedproxy.google.com/~r/BlastTheRight/~5/B6O4vuGmZY4/137-cardcheckfourpillars.mp3" type="audio/mpeg" /><itunes:explicit>no</itunes:explicit><itunes:subtitle>Today, you'll hear how to debunk a bald-faced lie the right is propagating about upcoming, critically important labor union legislation, the Employee Free Choice Act. This bill is labor's number one priority in Congress, and the right has declared war on </itunes:subtitle><itunes:author>Jack Clark</itunes:author><itunes:summary>Today, you'll hear how to debunk a bald-faced lie the right is propagating about upcoming, critically important labor union legislation, the Employee Free Choice Act. This bill is labor's number one priority in Congress, and the right has declared war on it.Next, I'll give you a short primer on what I call the four pillars, the four ways the right in the Western world economically exploits the </itunes:summary><itunes:keywords>politics,npr,christian,story,day,obama,bill,o,reilly,al,